How a data scientist explores a `.tsra` they received, with no prior knowledge of it — integrity
first, then structure, then the data itself. Every command is read-only and runs against the
conformance corpus (`multiblock_study.tsra`: an array `volume`, a table `roi`, and a provenance edge).
Digests are globbed with `[..]`; everything else is the verbatim transcript.

# === Is it intact? Verify the seal + every block digest before trusting a byte. ===

```
$ tessera verify ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra
OK  ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra verified (2 blocks)

```

The summary header carries a `seal` badge, but a bare `sealed✓` only proves the *manifest* is
intact — a block payload could still have been swapped. `inspect --verify` streams every block
through its digest (bounded memory) and reports the payload verdict too (`payloads✓`):

```
$ tessera inspect --verify ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra
tessera [..] · product=recon
id            [..]
name          [..]
timestamp     2024-01-01T00:00:00Z
producer      tessera/0.0.0
study         DUPLET-DP06-exam
content_hash  blake3:3b5d271b91ed2793445b561a709e38a469c7a73bdcd8ef8331e41ad7639498b8
manifest_hash blake3:8e18e39448ccf8b19315786a7b268a66a0372218b07ad21898d16ac61cb45042
seal          sealed✓
integrity     payloads✓ (2 blocks)
blocks        2
  - volume               Array blake3:6620c9be29593a0c4ac3439e420af4bf80866e761b664f1010a549dd70f0e2c9
  - roi                  Table blake3:827e49afe82ba77057cb4bc991ba53298aa4248315a216930329ee4ab5b28e4e
sources       1
  - derived_from <- recon-int16

```

# === Does it conform to its declared product schema (required fields + blocks)? ===

```
$ tessera schema ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra
product 'recon' — embedded schema v1.0 (A reconstructed image volume (CT/PET/μ-map).)
fields (13 declared):
  ● modality               required     coded       = "CT"
  · rescale_slope          optional     public      —
  · rescale_intercept      optional     public      —
  · patient_pseudonym      optional     identifying —
  · acquisition_uid        optional     identifying —
  ◐ study_instance_uid     recommended  identifying —
  ◐ series_instance_uid    recommended  identifying —
  ◐ study_date             recommended  sensitive   —
  ◐ manufacturer           recommended  public      —
  ◐ model_name             recommended  public      —
  ◐ kvp                    recommended  public      —
  ◐ slice_thickness        recommended  public      —
  ◐ pixel_spacing          recommended  public      —
OK  schema-valid: ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra

```

# === What's inside? One glance at the whole hierarchy — product, blocks, metadata, provenance. ===

```
$ tessera tree ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra
multiblock_study.tsra  ·  product=recon · schema=recon✓ · sealed✓
├── meta
│   └── modality = "CT"
├── schema  (recon v1.0)
│   ├── modality               required · coded
│   ├── rescale_slope          optional · public
│   ├── rescale_intercept      optional · public
│   ├── patient_pseudonym      optional · identifying
│   ├── acquisition_uid        optional · identifying
│   ├── study_instance_uid     recommended · identifying
│   ├── series_instance_uid    recommended · identifying
│   ├── study_date             recommended · sensitive
│   ├── manufacturer           recommended · public
│   ├── model_name             recommended · public
│   ├── kvp                    recommended · public
│   ├── slice_thickness        recommended · public
│   └── pixel_spacing          recommended · public
├── volume             array  int16  [16, 16, 16]  pcodec   blake3:6620c9be2959…
│   └── chunks [64, 64, 64]
├── roi                table  2 cols × 8 rows   blake3:827e49afe82b…
│   ├── label      u4
│   └── volume_ml  f4
├── sources
│   └── derived_from <- recon-int16
└── extra
    └── vendor_note  (string)

```

# === Drill into one node — the columns of the `roi` table. ===

```
$ tessera ls ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra roi
roi   table  2 cols × 8 rows
  label      u4
  volume_ml  f4

```

# === Trace provenance — what was this derived from? ===

```
$ tessera ls ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra sources
derived_from <- recon-int16

```

# === Pull the data you came for — just the columns you need, every row, as CSV. ===

```
$ tessera read ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra roi --column label --column volume_ml --all
label,volume_ml
0,0.5
1,1.75
2,3
3,4.25
4,5.5
5,6.75
6,8
7,9.25

```

# === Emit a FAIR discovery record (RO-Crate JSON) for your catalog / data portal. ===

```
$ tessera export ../../corpus/files/multiblock_study.tsra
{
  "@context": "https://w3id.org/ro/crate/1.1/context",
  "@graph": [
...
```
